235
00:09:38,871 --> 00:09:39,913
MRS. MATLIN:
LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE UPSET -

236
00:09:39,997 --> 00:09:41,999
I AM, TOO -

237
00:09:42,082 --> 00:09:43,584
BUT I DON'T THINK GOING
TO THE POLICE IS THE ANSWER.

238
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:44,918
SO SHE GETS OFF,
SCOTT-FREE?

239
00:09:45,002 --> 00:09:47,045
MAYA, I ASSURE YOU,
I WILL DEAL WITH THIS.

240
00:09:47,129 --> 00:09:48,881
(ANNOYED SIGH)

241
00:09:48,964 --> 00:09:50,674
MR. SIMPSON:
THANK YOU, EVERYONE.

242
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:52,593
HOPEFULLY, WE CAN PUT THIS
ALL BEHIND US.

243
00:09:54,428 --> 00:10:01,476
♪♪♪

244
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:03,061
(SIGHS)

245
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:07,608
VENI, VIDI, VICI!

246
00:10:09,568 --> 00:10:10,652
I CAME, I SAW,
I CONQUERED!

247
00:10:10,736 --> 00:10:12,029
MM-HMM.

248
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:13,572
WHERE'S DALLAS?

249
00:10:13,655 --> 00:10:15,157
UH, HE IS...

250
00:10:18,619 --> 00:10:20,579
AH!

251
00:10:20,662 --> 00:10:22,080
STOMACH FLU ALL CLEARED UP?

252
00:10:22,164 --> 00:10:24,333
YES, SIR,
I FEEL GREAT!

253
00:10:24,416 --> 00:10:25,501
GEOGRAPHY IS
MY FAVOURITE SUBJECT.

254
00:10:25,584 --> 00:10:27,961
(LAUGHS)

255
00:10:28,045 --> 00:10:28,879
I TOLD YOU, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT ME!

256
00:10:28,962 --> 00:10:31,465
MIKE DALLAS IS ALIVE
AND WELL!

257
00:10:31,548 --> 00:10:33,050
I CAN'T WAIT
TO SEE THIS.

258
00:10:35,511 --> 00:10:36,136
HAVE YOU BEEN DRINKING?!

259
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:39,056
NO! (LAUGHS)

260
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:42,392
OKAY, MAYBE ONE...
CASE.

261
00:10:42,476 --> 00:10:44,561
DREW:
OKAY, NO PROBLEM.

262
00:10:44,645 --> 00:10:46,897
WE CAN DO THIS,
JUST...

263
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:48,482
PUT THIS ON!

264
00:10:49,942 --> 00:10:51,235
OH MAN,
ARE WE GONNA BE GHOSTS?

265
00:10:51,318 --> 00:10:53,237
OH, THIS'LL BE SPOOKY!

266
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:55,948
OKAY, NEW PLAN.

267
00:10:56,031 --> 00:10:57,991
YOU BE CAESAR
AND I'LL BE BRUTUS.

268
00:10:59,409 --> 00:11:00,911
HEY, DREW,

269
00:11:02,287 --> 00:11:04,706
YOU WERE RIGHT, MAN,

270
00:11:04,790 --> 00:11:07,084
I'M A FAILURE.
SHHH!

271
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:08,460
I ADMIT IT,

272
00:11:08,544 --> 00:11:11,672
I. AM. A FAILURE.

273
00:11:11,755 --> 00:11:13,549
SHH! DALLAS, OKAY,
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

274
00:11:13,632 --> 00:11:15,300
JUST PRETEND TO BE
DEAD FOR ME.

275
00:11:17,803 --> 00:11:19,304
ALAS!
CAESAR AND BRUTUS!

276
00:11:22,641 --> 00:11:25,811
HERE GOES NOTHING.

277
00:11:25,894 --> 00:11:27,312
THE RISE OF THE ROMAN EMPIRE
CAME AFTER THE DEATH

278
00:11:27,396 --> 00:11:28,856
OF JULIUS CAESAR,

279
00:11:28,939 --> 00:11:31,108
WHO WAS BETRAYED
BY HIS FRIEND, BRUTUS.

280
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:32,693
UNGH!

281
00:11:35,445 --> 00:11:36,947
WHY, BRUTUS, WHY?

282
00:11:39,116 --> 00:11:40,909
(STUDENTS CHUCKLE)

283
00:11:40,993 --> 00:11:41,994
BRUTUS THOUGHT IT WAS HIS DUTY
TO KILL HIS FRIEND

284
00:11:42,077 --> 00:11:43,078
TO SAVE THE PEOPLE OF ROME.

285
00:11:43,161 --> 00:11:44,830
DALLAS:
WHOA!

286
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:48,667
DESPITE HOW MUCH BRUTUS
HAD COME TO LOVE CAESAR...

287
00:11:48,750 --> 00:11:50,502
CAESAR'S GHOST CAME BACK
TO SAY THAT HE-

288
00:11:50,586 --> 00:11:51,628
THAT HE FORGAVE BRUTUS!

289
00:11:51,712 --> 00:11:53,213
(RETCHING)

290
00:11:54,298 --> 00:11:55,799
(VOMITING NOISILY)

291
00:12:00,929 --> 00:12:02,723
LOOK AT THAT.

292
00:12:02,806 --> 00:12:04,516
CAESAR HAD THE STOMACH FLU
AFTER ALL.

293
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,101
(LAUGHS)

294
00:12:12,399 --> 00:12:14,985
I'M GUESSING THE MEETING
DIDN'T GO WELL?

295
00:12:15,068 --> 00:12:16,069
MY MOM DOESN'T WANT
TO PRESS CRIMINAL CHARGES

296
00:12:16,153 --> 00:12:18,947
BECAUSE ZOE SAID
SHE WAS SORRY.

297
00:12:19,031 --> 00:12:20,157
(MILES PLAYS BLUES RIFF)

298
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,742
I WANT ZOE DEAD!

299
00:12:22,993 --> 00:12:24,870
♪♪♪

300
00:12:24,953 --> 00:12:26,705
♪ SO DEAD ♪

301
00:12:26,788 --> 00:12:28,749
(PLAYS BLUES REFRAIN)

302
00:12:28,832 --> 00:12:29,833
♪ REALLY DEAD ♪

303
00:12:29,917 --> 00:12:31,752
(PLAYS BLUES REFRAIN)

304
00:12:31,835 --> 00:12:32,794
I CAN'T STAND
ALL THESE RUMOURS

305
00:12:32,878 --> 00:12:35,005
AND FAKE PICS OF ME
IN MY BLOOMERS.

306
00:12:35,088 --> 00:12:36,089
(LAUGHS)
THERE YOU GO!

307
00:12:36,173 --> 00:12:37,758
(MILES PLAYS BLUES REFRAIN)

308
00:12:37,841 --> 00:12:39,843
I'VE GOT A FAN PAGE
THAT'S PHOTOSHOPPED

309
00:12:39,927 --> 00:12:41,929
AND SIMPSON SAYS
IT CAN'T BE STOPPED.

310
00:12:42,012 --> 00:12:43,722
♪♪♪

311
00:12:43,805 --> 00:12:46,808
♪ YOU WANT HER DEAD ♪

312
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:49,353
♪ REALLY, REALLY DEAD ♪

313
00:12:49,436 --> 00:12:51,230
♪ I'VE GOT THE LYING, ♪

314
00:12:51,313 --> 00:12:52,981
♪ SNEAKY BITCH-IS-GONNA-
ROT-IN-HELL ♪

315
00:12:53,065 --> 00:12:54,525
♪ BACKSTABBING FRIEND BLUES ♪

316
00:12:54,608 --> 00:12:56,401
♪♪♪

317
00:12:56,485 --> 00:12:57,986
YEAH!

318
00:12:58,654 --> 00:13:00,155
(BOTH LAUGH)

319
00:13:01,448 --> 00:13:02,908
MILES:
SEE? DON'T YOU FEEL BETTER?

320
00:13:02,991 --> 00:13:04,368
I'D FEEL BETTER

321
00:13:04,451 --> 00:13:07,079
IF EVERYONE KNEW
HOW EVIL ZOE WAS.

322
00:13:07,162 --> 00:13:08,539
MAYBE YOU NEED TO FIND
A WAY TO...

323
00:13:08,622 --> 00:13:10,457
ENLIGHTEN THEM.

324
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:16,964
♪♪♪

325
00:13:17,047 --> 00:13:18,549
DREW:
HEY, DALLAS,
WAIT UP, MAN!

326
00:13:20,092 --> 00:13:21,760
CONSIDERING THE CIRCUMSTANCES,

327
00:13:21,844 --> 00:13:24,137
I THINK THAT WENT PRETTY WELL,
DON'T YOU?

328
00:13:24,221 --> 00:13:25,931
DOESN'T MATTER.

329
00:13:26,014 --> 00:13:27,724
THAT GHOST THING
WAS GENIUS.

330
00:13:27,808 --> 00:13:29,309
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

331
00:13:31,228 --> 00:13:33,981
I'M MOVING BACK
TO GUELPH.

332
00:13:34,064 --> 00:13:35,065
WHAT? WHY?
NO, YOU CAN'T, MAN!

333
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:37,901
YOU THINK I WANT TO,

334
00:13:37,985 --> 00:13:40,237
GO BACK HOME
A BIG LOSER?

335
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,406
LOOK, LOSING HOCKEY SUCKS,
I GET IT-

336
00:13:42,489 --> 00:13:43,532
I'VE DREAMT ABOUT
GETTING INTO THE NHL

337
00:13:43,615 --> 00:13:46,410
MY ENTIRE LIFE.

338
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:48,120
WHO AM I WITHOUT HOCKEY?

339
00:13:49,872 --> 00:13:51,164
AFTER MY CONCUSSION,

340
00:13:51,248 --> 00:13:54,710
I THOUGHT THERE WAS
NOTHING FOR ME.

341
00:13:54,793 --> 00:13:56,295
NOW I'M THE PRESIDENT...

342
00:13:58,589 --> 00:14:01,425
AND YOU'RE BETTER
AT WAY MORE STUFF THAN ME.

343
00:14:01,508 --> 00:14:04,803
LIKE WHAT, DRINKING?

344
00:14:04,887 --> 00:14:07,139
MAKING A FOOL
OUT OF MYSELF?

345
00:14:07,222 --> 00:14:08,390
KEEPING ME
OUT OF TROUBLE.

346
00:14:08,473 --> 00:14:09,975
(GROANS)

347
00:14:13,020 --> 00:14:14,730
I HAVE NO REASON
TO STAY.

348
00:14:16,690 --> 00:14:19,902
YEAH, YOU DO.

349
00:14:19,985 --> 00:14:21,904
I ALREADY LOST ONE BROTHER
THIS YEAR,

350
00:14:23,697 --> 00:14:25,199
I CAN'T LOSE ANOTHER.

351
00:14:27,951 --> 00:14:38,879
♪♪♪

352
00:14:39,296 --> 00:14:43,258
♪ I will always have open eyes ♪

353
00:14:46,345 --> 00:14:48,180
♪ You've come alive ♪

354
00:14:51,141 --> 00:14:55,646
♪ I will hold you away ♪

355
00:14:55,729 --> 00:14:57,231
OR DO PEOPLE CHANGE?

356
00:14:59,107 --> 00:15:00,609
♪ My dear ♪

357
00:15:03,529 --> 00:15:06,698
(SIGHS)

358
00:15:06,782 --> 00:15:09,409
MS. OH:
WE HAVE TIME FOR ONE MORE
SONGWRITING ASSIGNMENT TODAY.

359
00:15:09,493 --> 00:15:11,286
UM, ACTUALLY,
I WROTE ANOTHER NEW SONG.

360
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:14,122
OKAY, GIVE IT UP
FOR THE PROLIFIC MAYA MATLIN!

361
00:15:14,206 --> 00:15:15,165
MILES:
WAIT, ARE YOU SURE YOU WANNA
GO THROUGH WITH THIS?

362
00:15:15,249 --> 00:15:16,834
I WASN'T BEING
ENTIRELY SERIOUS.

363
00:15:16,917 --> 00:15:18,418
I WAS.

364
00:15:20,295 --> 00:15:23,173
OKAY, THIS SONG
IS ABOUT KARMA...

365
00:15:23,257 --> 00:15:26,218
AND, SPOILER ALERT,
IT SUCKS.

366
00:15:26,301 --> 00:15:27,803
(STRUMMING CHORDS)

367
00:15:30,013 --> 00:15:31,390
♪ YOU WERE A SUPERSTAR ♪

368
00:15:31,473 --> 00:15:34,226
♪ NOW YOU'RE A HAS-BEEN ♪

369
00:15:34,309 --> 00:15:37,187
♪ THOUGHT WE WERE FRIENDS
BUT YOU WERE JUST ACTING ♪

370
00:15:37,271 --> 00:15:38,897
♪ ONE DAY I'LL WATCH YOU DIE ♪

371
00:15:38,981 --> 00:15:40,858
♪ MAYBE IN YOUR SLEEP ♪

372
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:44,361
♪ PUT YOU SIX FEET UNDER
SO YOU DON'T MAKE A PEEP! ♪

373
00:15:44,444 --> 00:15:46,196
MS. OH:
MAYA!

374
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:47,865
♪ WATCH YOUR BACK ♪

375
00:15:47,948 --> 00:15:51,034
♪ YOU'RE DEAD WITH A CAPITAL
D-EEE EEE-EEE-EEE ♪

376
00:15:51,118 --> 00:15:53,495
MS. MATLIN!

377
00:15:53,579 --> 00:15:56,164
♪ THE WORLD WILL BE A MUCH
BETTER PLACE WITHOUT YOU ♪

378
00:15:56,248 --> 00:15:58,417
♪ ZOE-EEE-EEE-EEE-EEE ♪

379
00:16:00,294 --> 00:16:01,795
MS. OH:
THAT'S ENOUGH!

380
00:16:05,591 --> 00:16:07,467
MAYA:
LET ME GUESS,
GO TO THE OFFICE?

381
00:16:07,551 --> 00:16:09,178
MS. OH:
YES.

382
00:16:09,261 --> 00:16:18,645
♪♪♪

383
00:16:18,729 --> 00:16:20,230
NEED ANY HELP?

384
00:16:22,774 --> 00:16:23,358
IF YOU STILL GOT SPACE
FOR AN EX-HOCKEY PLAYER

385
00:16:23,442 --> 00:16:24,943
WITH NO PROSPECTS.

386
00:16:28,030 --> 00:16:30,449
DEPENDS.

387
00:16:30,532 --> 00:16:31,909
ARE YOU DONE
WITH ALL THE DRINKING?

388
00:16:31,992 --> 00:16:33,493
AFTER THIS AFTERNOON?
YEAH.

389
00:16:35,204 --> 00:16:37,372
WHAT ABOUT THE GIRLS?

390
00:16:37,456 --> 00:16:38,582
I CAN'T HELP IT
IF THE LADIES LOVE ME!

391
00:16:38,665 --> 00:16:40,959
(BOTH LAUGH)

392
00:16:41,043 --> 00:16:42,836
NEXT TIME,
UH...

393
00:16:42,920 --> 00:16:43,212
TRY TO LEARN A GIRL'S NAME
BEFORE YOU BRING HER HOME,

394
00:16:43,295 --> 00:16:45,130
OKAY?

395
00:16:45,214 --> 00:16:46,715
SURE THING, AUDRA.

396
00:16:49,343 --> 00:16:50,844
(DALLAS SIGHS)

397
00:16:53,013 --> 00:16:54,848
SUSPENDED, MAYA,

398
00:16:54,932 --> 00:16:56,391
FOR THREATENING
A GIRL'S LIFE?!

399
00:16:56,475 --> 00:16:58,894
IT WAS A SONG!

400
00:16:58,977 --> 00:17:01,396
YOU REALLY THINK
I'M CAPABLE OF MURDER?

401
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:03,565
YOU-YOU ARE GROUNDED,
OBVIOUSLY,

402
00:17:03,649 --> 00:17:06,568
WHICH MEANS NO TV
AND NO INTERNET!

403
00:17:06,652 --> 00:17:09,446
YOU DON'T GET IT,
DO YOU?!

404
00:17:09,530 --> 00:17:11,865
I WAS GROPED
BY A RANDOM JERK TODAY

405
00:17:11,949 --> 00:17:14,243
AND PEOPLE LOOK AT ME
LIKE I HAVE A DISEASE,

406
00:17:14,326 --> 00:17:16,078
AND ZOE GETS TO GO
AROUND LAUGHING

407
00:17:16,161 --> 00:17:18,163
AND FLIPPING HER HAIR,
LIKE OMG!

408
00:17:18,247 --> 00:17:19,248
YOU CAN'T LET THEM
HURT YOU,

409
00:17:19,331 --> 00:17:21,625
YOU HAVE TO TURN
THE OTHER CHEEK!

410
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:25,087
MOM, DO YOU REALIZE
HOW HARD THAT IS

411
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:26,922
WHEN THEY'RE AT SCHOOL
AND ONLINE?

412
00:17:27,005 --> 00:17:28,340
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SINK
TO THEIR LEVEL.

413
00:17:28,423 --> 00:17:30,467
YOU ARE BETTER THAN THAT.

414
00:17:30,551 --> 00:17:31,552
ARE WE DONE?

415
00:17:31,635 --> 00:17:33,136
NO!

416
00:17:37,516 --> 00:17:40,102
LOOK, IF YOU WANNA PRESS
CRIMINAL CHARGES AGAINST ZOE,

417
00:17:40,185 --> 00:17:42,062
WE CAN.

418
00:17:42,145 --> 00:17:43,856
SERIOUSLY?

419
00:17:43,939 --> 00:17:45,440
IT'S GONNA BE LONG
AND IT'S GONNA BE DIFFICULT,

420
00:17:45,524 --> 00:17:48,902
BUT I WANT YOU TO KNOW
THAT I AM ON YOUR SIDE.

421
00:17:48,986 --> 00:17:50,487
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

422
00:17:56,243 --> 00:17:57,744
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

423
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:05,252
ALLI:
AHEM!

424
00:18:06,962 --> 00:18:09,047
HEY, LEO,
CAN WE TALK?

425
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:13,302
ALLI.

426
00:18:13,385 --> 00:18:15,804
I CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW HAPPY I AM TO SEE YOU.

427
00:18:18,599 --> 00:18:20,684
YOU AND I HAVE
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

428
00:18:20,767 --> 00:18:22,436
ABSOLUMENT.

429
00:18:22,519 --> 00:18:25,022
(SHAKY SIGH)

430
00:18:25,105 --> 00:18:26,023
BUT IF WE'RE GOING
TO BE TOGETHER,

431
00:18:26,106 --> 00:18:27,482
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO GET THERAPY.

432
00:18:27,566 --> 00:18:29,610
I CAN DO THAT.

433
00:18:29,693 --> 00:18:32,029
AND I STILL WANT
TO GO TO M.I.T.

434
00:18:32,112 --> 00:18:33,822
M.I.T. IS YOUR DREAM.

435
00:18:33,906 --> 00:18:36,074
I DON'T WANT TO STAND
IN YOUR WAY.

436
00:18:36,158 --> 00:18:37,910
AND PROMISE ME, LEO,
IF YOU EVER GET UPSET,

437
00:18:37,993 --> 00:18:40,913
THAT YOU'LL TALK TO ME.

438
00:18:40,996 --> 00:18:44,124
BECAUSE IF YOU EVER
HIT ME AGAIN,

439
00:18:44,208 --> 00:18:45,792
I'M GONE.

440
00:18:45,876 --> 00:18:47,377
NO MORE CHANCES.

441
00:18:48,795 --> 00:18:50,422
NEVER AGAIN.
YOU HAVE MY WORD.

442
00:18:52,466 --> 00:18:54,551
YOU CAN'T LET ME DOWN,
LEO.

443
00:18:54,635 --> 00:18:56,303
NOT AGAIN.

444
00:18:56,386 --> 00:18:57,888
NO.

445
00:18:58,931 --> 00:19:02,518
(CELLO MUSIC PLAYS)

446
00:19:05,854 --> 00:19:10,817
♪♪♪

447
00:19:10,901 --> 00:19:12,402
(KNOCKING)

448
00:19:18,951 --> 00:19:20,452
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

449
00:19:21,870 --> 00:19:24,331
I JUST WANTED
TO APOLOGIZE.

450
00:19:24,414 --> 00:19:26,875
I FEEL LIKE I PUSHED YOU
TO DO THAT SONG.

451
00:19:26,959 --> 00:19:28,126
ZOE RUINED MY LIFE,
SHE DESERVES IT.

452
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:30,087
SHE'S JUST JEALOUS

453
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:32,089
BECAUSE YOU ARE TALENTED,
AND FUNNY,

454
00:19:32,172 --> 00:19:34,258
AND AWESOME IN WAYS
SHE'LL NEVER BE.

455
00:19:34,341 --> 00:19:35,801
YOU DON'T HAVE TO SAY THINGS
TO MAKE ME FEEL BETTER.

456
00:19:35,884 --> 00:19:38,011
I'M NOT,
TRUST ME.

457
00:19:48,146 --> 00:19:49,648
(BOTH LAUGH)

458
00:19:51,775 --> 00:19:54,194
SCHOOL'S GONNA SUCK
WITHOUT YOU.

459
00:19:54,278 --> 00:19:56,530
MRS. MATLIN:
MAYA, I TOLD YOU NO TV!

460
00:19:56,613 --> 00:19:58,115
SHE'S COMING, GO!
WAIT, NO!

461
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:01,201
(LAUGHS)

462
00:20:09,209 --> 00:20:10,711
I-I SWEAR I HEARD THE TV.

463
00:20:13,046 --> 00:20:14,089
OH, WELL, MAYBE YOU SHOULD
GET YOUR HEARING CHECKED.

464
00:20:14,173 --> 00:20:15,841
YOU KNOW,
YOU ARE GETTING OLD.

465
00:20:15,924 --> 00:20:17,426
VERY FUNNY.

466
00:20:19,428 --> 00:20:21,889
SO HAVE YOU THOUGHT ANY MORE
ABOUT PRESSING CHARGES?

467
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:26,101
(SIGHS) WELL...

468
00:20:28,103 --> 00:20:30,856
JUST BECAUSE ZOE'S EVIL
DOESN'T MEAN I HAVE TO BE.

469
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:34,067
I WANNA MOVE ON,

470
00:20:34,151 --> 00:20:36,069
AND I HAVE THINGS
TO LOOK FORWARD TO.

471
00:20:37,362 --> 00:20:38,864
I'M GLAD TO HEAR IT.

472
00:20:44,119 --> 00:20:45,621
(LAUGHS)

